  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Process Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Provide technical leadership in lab and pilot experiments and lead process & design engineering through PFD/P&ID, Aspen modelling, heat & material balance, equipment sizing, vendor packages, and PHA. Translate experimental learnings into commercial‑scale designs.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Plan/oversee pilot operations: troubleshooting, test planning, data validation, scale‑up evaluation.</li><li>Define KPIs & success criteria; enforce reproducible methods and robust documentation.</li><li>Lead conceptual & detailed PFD/P&ID; draft design basis and project schedules.</li><li>Build/validate Aspen Plus (or equivalent) models; produce H&MB for plant configurations.</li><li>Perform sizing (reactors, columns, pumps, tanks, instrumentation) and develop equipment lists/specs.</li><li>Coordinate vendor engagement; review Basic Engineering Packages; lead FAT/SAT, commissioning.</li><li>Prepare cost estimates, feed into TEA.</li><li>Lead/participate PHA/HAZOP; author SOPs for start‑up, shutdown, emergency & sampling.</li><li>Champion safety, continuous improvement, and knowledge transfer.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Chemical/Process Engineering.</li><li>8–12+ years in process design & scale‑up, Aspen modelling, vendor mgmt., and pilot testing.</li><li>Strong technical writing and cross‑functional collaboration.</li></ul>",
